text.tspan: Excess mortality during COVID-19: Number of deaths from all causes
compared to previous years, United States
Shown is how the number of weekly or monthly deaths in 2020–2021 differs from the number of deaths in the same period
over the years 2015–2019. The reported number of deaths might not count all deaths that occurred due to incomplete
coverage and delays in death reporting.
Source: Human Mortality Database (2021), World Mortality Dataset (2021)
Note: Comparisons across countries are affected by differences in the completeness of death reporting. Details can be found at our Excess
